description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 5 Registered Nurse to join our friendly and supportive critical care team based in Critical Care. We are looking for a nurse who is &lt;strong&gt;able to demonstrate recent and relevant experience at Band 5 level in an acute hospital environment.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Critical Care Department consists of a 7 bedded Intensive Care Unit and an 9 bed High Dependency Unit. We deliver high quality, patient focused care for patients who are level 1 to level 3. We have a dedicated outreach service and provide a Critical Care follow up service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for staff who are flexible and will be working across both ITU and HDU in order to develop their skills and support service needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In exchange for this commitment we can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a structured supernumerary orientation program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the support of our Practice Development Nurse&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;access to university courses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;the opportunity to complete the National Competency Framework for Adult Critical Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Laura Clyde - Senior Sister - Critical care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;laura.clyde@ldh.nhs.uk   01582 497249&lt;/p&gt;
